Including Plots

ggplot()+
  geom_polygon(data = world,
               aes(x = long, 
                   y = lat, 
                   group = group,
               fill = region), # fills in polygon with color
               color = "black") + # outlines in color
  guides(fill = FALSE)+
  theme_minimal()+
  guides(fill = FALSE)+
  theme(panel.background = element_rect(fill = "lightblue"))+ # fills in ocean (background) blue
  coord_map(projection = "sinusoidal",
            xlim = c(-180,180))
## Warning: `guides(<scale> = FALSE)` is deprecated. Please use `guides(<scale> = "none")` instead.
## `guides(<scale> = FALSE)` is deprecated. Please use `guides(<scale> = "none")` instead.

CA_data<-states %>% 
  filter(region == "california")

ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = CA_data,
               aes(x = long,
                   y = lat,
                   group = group,
               fill = region), # to put a specific color, put outside of aes
               color = "black") +
  coord_map() +
  theme_void() # remeoves lines and background

## # A tibble: 6 × 2
##   County         Population
##   <chr>               <dbl>
## 1 los angeles      10081570
## 2 san diego         3316073
## 3 orange            3168044
## 4 riverside         2411439
## 5 san bernardino    2149031
## 6 santa clara       1927470
CApop_county<-popdata %>% 
  select("subregion" = County, Population) %>% 
  inner_join(counties) %>% 
  filter(region == "california")
## Joining, by = "subregion"
head(CApop_county)
## # A tibble: 6 × 7
##   subregion   Population  long   lat group order region    
##   <chr>            <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <int> <chr>     
## 1 los angeles   10081570 -119.  34.8   175  7827 california
## 2 los angeles   10081570 -118.  34.8   175  7828 california
## 3 los angeles   10081570 -118.  34.8   175  7829 california
## 4 los angeles   10081570 -118.  34.6   175  7830 california
## 5 los angeles   10081570 -118.  34.6   175  7831 california
## 6 los angeles   10081570 -118.  34.5   175  7832 california
ggplot()+
  geom_polygon(data = CApop_county,
               aes(x = long,
                   y = lat,
                   group = group,
                   fill = Population),
               color = "black") +
  geom_point(data = stars,
             aes(x = long,
                 y = lat,
                 size = star_no))+
  coord_map()+
  theme_void()+
  scale_fill_gradient(trans = "log10")+
  labs(size = "# stars/m2")

ggsave(here("Week_7","Output","CApop.pdf"))
